# Backend Routes Module

## PURPOSE
API endpoint definitions and request handlers.
Defines all REST API routes for the application.

## CONTAINS
- auth.js: Authentication routes (register, login, logout)
- user.js: User profile and settings routes
- payment.js: Payment processing routes (Stripe webhooks)
- subscription.js: Subscription data CRUD operations

## ROUTE STRUCTURE
### Auth Routes
- POST /api/auth/register - Create new user account
- POST /api/auth/login - User login, return JWT
- POST /api/auth/logout - Invalidate token
- POST /api/auth/refresh - Refresh JWT token

### User Routes
- GET /api/user/profile - Get user profile
- PUT /api/user/profile - Update user profile
- GET /api/user/status - Get payment status and run count

### Payment Routes
- POST /api/payment/create-checkout - Create Stripe checkout session
- POST /api/payment/webhook - Handle Stripe webhooks
- GET /api/payment/verify - Verify payment status

### Subscription Routes
- POST /api/subscriptions - Save scanned subscriptions
- GET /api/subscriptions - Get user's subscriptions
- DELETE /api/subscriptions/:id - Remove subscription

## REFERENCES
- Parent: /backend/.windsurf
- Root: /.windsurf
- Uses: /backend/models/*, /backend/middleware/*

## RULES
- All routes except auth must require authentication
- Validate request bodies with middleware
- Return consistent error responses
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Implement rate limiting on sensitive endpoints
